Program: Great Lives
Title: John Ford
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01h6678
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 28 Dec 2018
John Ford had a monumental Hollywood career - over 140 films, Oscars he never turned up to receive, and a blunt way of approaching the business that made him enemies as well as friends. He stood up once at a meeting and said simply, "My name's John Ford, I make westerns." Critic Ed Buscombe also joins Matthew Parris and we hear archive of the tough-talking director John Ford. From 2012. Producer: Miles Warde. Show less